.TH IBCHECKLINKS 8 "Oct 30, 2010" "Pragmatic Infiniband Utilities" "Infiniband Diagnostics"

.SH NAME
ibchecklinks \- scan ibfabric and check agains ib fabric config

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ibchecklinks [options]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
ibchecklinks scans an attached IB fabric, reads the ib fabric config file, and
compares the two.  Checks performed include invalid cabling, downed/disabled
ports, invalid speed, and invalid width's.

.SH OPTIONS

.PP
.TP
\fB\-config, \-c <ibfabricconf>\fR
Specify an alternate config file (default: @PIU_CONFIG_PATH@/pragmaticIB/ibfabricconf.xml)

\fB\-\-warn_dup, \-w\fR
print warning about duplicate links found in fabric config

\fB\-\-downhosts <hostlist>\fR
specify hosts which are known to be off

.TP
\fB\-S <guid>\fR
Output only the switch specified by <guid> (hex format)
.TP
\fB\-D <direct_route>\fR
Output only the switch specified by the direct route path.
.TP
\fB\-\-outstanding_smps, \-o <outstanding_smps>\fR
specify the number of outstanding smps on the wire.  This option can greatly
increase the scalabily of the scan.  However, specifing this number too high
may result in VL15 drops across the fabric and result in incresed retries to
gather the data.  This is because Nodes are only required to have buffer space
for 1 VL15 packet.
.TP
\fB\-\-hops \-n <hops>\fR
hops to progress away from node given in -G,-S, or -D, default == 0
.TP
\fB\-\-node\-name\-map <map>\fR
specify alternate node name map
.TP
\fB\-C <ca_name>\fR    use the specified ca_name for the search.
.TP
\fB\-P <ca_port>\fR    use the specified ca_port for the search.


